article.headline: Drexel 79, Delaware 69
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Samme Givens scored 19 points and led four Drexel players in double figures in a 79-69 win over Delaware on Tuesday. Jamie Harris added 14 points, while Leon Spencer had 11 and Scott Rodgers had 10. The Dragons (9-8) won their fourth in a row. Alphonso Dawson led Delaware (8-12) with 20 points, along with seven rebounds Drexel took an eight-point lead at the end of the first half after shooting 46 percent from the field. Delaware cut the margin to one by late in the second half, trailing 52-51 with 6:58 to go. But the Dragons outscored the Blue Hens 27-18 in the closing minutes. Marc Egerson added 14 points and nine rebounds for Delaware.
